To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records — restricted with the date range of April 12, 2023 to the time that this request is processed:
* Any official proposals, plans, agreements, reports, or recommendations created by Kathleen Corradi (the Citywide Director of Rodent Mitigation, aka NYC's First-Ever 'Rat Czar'). These documents may be called something similar to the following:
Rodent Mitigation Strategy Proposal
Cross-Agency Coordination Protocol
Community Engagement Plan
Private Sector Collaboration Agreement
Health Impact Assessment Report
Data Analysis and Progress Report
Legislative and Policy Recommendation
Budget Proposal and Resource Allocation Plan
Training Manuals and Protocols

When completing this request, please prioritize whichever records would take the least amount of time to be located and released. I would like these records in electronic format, sent via email or other digital method, and again, please release documents on a rolling basis, as they become available.

If you determine that any of the information qualifies for an exemption from disclosure, I ask you to note whether the exemption is discretionary, and if so whether it is necessary in this case to exercise your discretion to withhold the information. In any event, please provide a signed notification citing the legal authorities on which you rely if you determine that any of the information is exempt and will not be disclosed.

Also, I am a member of the news media as a reporter for Business Insider, and the requested documents are in the public interest and not being made for commercial purposes. Therefore, I ask that all fees are waived in the processing of my request. If fees associated with this request will be in excess of $25, kindly notify me in advance of fulfilling this request. As I am making this request as a journalist and this information is timely, I would appreciate your communicating with me if you have questions regarding this request.

Thanks again, and if there are any questions about my request, can provide any clarification that will help expedite the processing of my request, please contact me at email address. I am also happy to hop on the phone.

I look forward to your reply within 5 business days, as the statute requires and an even more prompt reply if you can make a determination without having to review the records in question.

Thank you for your time and attention to this matter.

Best,
Caroline

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Any and all documents pertaining to reports, data, structures, procedures, incident reports for geographical coordinates: 30 (degrees) 19.567' and West 88 (degrees) 31.360' on March 22, 2023 at or around 9:30PM. This includes construction projects ongoing in the area at or around this time by the US Coast Guard and/or entities contracted by such.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Marshall Goff

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Florida Sunshine Law, I hereby request the following records — restricted with the date range of 01/01/2020 to the time that this request is processed:
* A log of all calls and incidents reported to the Nuisance Alligator Hotline from its inception through the date this request is processed. Please include the time and date of the call, any available description of the phone call, and any action that was taken as a result. Please redact any personally-identifying information.
* A copy of any call logs or materials used to track incoming complaints to FWC’s Nuisance Alligator Hotline 866-FWC-GATOR (866-392-4286).
* If there exist any weekly, monthly, quarterly, or annual reports regarding the hotline, I will accept those instead of the above-requested records.
* Any and all records regarding the number of calls the Nuisance Alligator Hotline has received, the subject of the calls, resolution offered
* The current written guidelines developed by AZGFD pertaining to the handling of hotline calls and referrals. These guidelines would specifically include the two documents entitled "Nuisance Alligator Hotline Program Orientation" and "Nuisance Alligator Hotline Screening Protocols", as well as any additional guidelines the FWC may utilize.

When completing this request, please prioritize whichever records would take the least amount of time to be located and released. I would like these records in electronic format, sent via email or other digital method, and again, please release documents on a rolling basis, as they become available.

If you determine that any of the information qualifies for an exemption from disclosure, I ask you to note whether the exemption is discretionary, and if so whether it is necessary in this case to exercise your discretion to withhold the information. In any event, please provide a signed notification citing the legal authorities on which you rely if you determine that any of the information is exempt and will not be disclosed.

Also, I am a member of the news media as a reporter for Business Insider, and the requested documents are in the public interest and not being made for commercial purposes. Therefore, I ask that all fees are waived in the processing of my request. If fees associated with this request will be in excess of $25, kindly notify me in advance of fulfilling this request. As I am making this request as a journalist and this information is timely, I would appreciate your communicating with me if you have questions regarding this request.

Thanks again, and if there are any questions about my request, can provide any clarification that will help expedite the processing of my request, please contact me at email address. I am also happy to hop on the phone.

I look forward to your reply within 10 business days and an even more prompt reply if you can make a determination without having to review the records in question.

Thank you for your time and attention to this matter.

Best,
Caroline
